HEADWORD: Tutsan
<hw>Tut"san</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>toutesaine</ets>; <ets>tout</ets>, <ets>toute</ets>, all (L.
<ets>totus</ets>) + <ets>sain</ets>, <ets>saine</ets>, sound, healthy,
L. <ets>sanus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the genus
<gen>Hypericum</gen> (<spn>Hypericum Androsoemum</spn>), from which a
healing ointment is prepared in Spain; -- called also
<altname>parkleaves</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
